                    <h4 class="first">Punishment for Careless Driving</h4>
                    <h4 class="second">The Law in Ontario</h4>
                    <h5>HTA S. 130</h5>
                    <p>Every person is guilty of a careless driving offence if driven a vehicle or street car on the highway without due care and attention, or without reasonable consideration for other persons using the highway. R.S.O. 1990, c.H.8, s.130 <br/> Ontario Careless Driving Penalty</p>
                    <ul>
                    <li>6 Ontario Demerit Points</li>
                    <li>A Fine not less than $400 and not more than $1000</li>
                    <li>Imprisonment for a term not more than 6 months, or both</li>
                    <li>The Driver’s license may also be suspended for a period of not more than 2 years</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4 class="first">Legal Help for Your Careless Driving Ticket in Toronto</h3>
                    <p>Obviously, there are many gray areas associated with these types of traffic tickets in Ontario. There are many reasons in which your charges may be lessened or completely cleared with the help of a solid legal defense for your actions.</p>
                    <p>How are we able to help you win your careless driving charge? First, we order your full disclosure, meaning all of the evidence against you.  This information is used to build a robust legal defense for you using case law. Our experienced paralegals and clerks devote the time necessary to not only gather all of the information about the incident and your defense, but we also are available to answer all of your questions about the legal process.</p>
                    <p>We are incredibly successful when it comes to having careless driving tickets completely withdrawn in Toronto for our clients. Contact us today to learn more about how we can protect you and your driving privileges.</p>
