                <div>
                    <h3>Disobey Amber Light - Amber Fail to Stop</h3>
                    <hr/>
                    <p>Many Ontario drivers do not know they cannot proceed through a traffic intersection on an amber light. This confusion can lead to a conviction and demerit points against a driver’s license.<br/>The Law in Ontario:</p>                    
                    <h4 class="first">HTA s. 144(15)</h4>
                    <p>Every driver approaching a traffic control signal showing a circular amber indication and facing the indication shall stop his or her vehicle if he or she can do so safely, otherwise he or she may proceed with caution.</p>
                    <h4 class="first">The Penalty in Ontario:</h4>
                    <ul>
                    <li>3 demerit points</li>
                    <li>3 year conviction</li>
                    <li>Fine $150</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3>Disobey Stop Sign Ontario & The Law</h3>
                    <hr/>
                    <h4 class="first">HTA s.136 (1)(a)</h4>
                    <p>Every Driver or street car operator approaching a stop sign at an intersection,</p>
                    <p>a) shall stop his or her vehicle or street car at a marked stop line or, if none, then immediately before    entering the nearest crosswalk or, if none, then immediately before entering the intersection;</p>
                    <h4 class="first">Penalty in Ontario</h4>
                    <ul>
                    <li>3 Demerit Points</li>
                    <li>Set Fine: $110.00 including government surcharge</li>
