                <div>
                    <h3>Driving Under Suspension Tickets Toronto</h3>
                    <hr/>
                    <h4 class="first">How to Act When Your Driver’s License Is Suspended</h4>
                    <p>The first thing you should do after a license suspension in Ontario is call Get Legal Help for a     consultation. There are many complex reasons that can lead to a driver’s license being suspended, an    experienced traffic ticket lawyers or paralegals will examine every aspect of your driving to determine if     you can fight the charges that led to the suspension. If your license remains suspended, we will take every     legal action necessary to help you have it reinstated as soon as possible.</p>
                    <h4 class="first">Reasons Driver’s Licenses May Be Suspended</h4>
                    <p>There are numerous reasons your driver’s license could be suspended in Ontario. Common causes include:</p>
                    <ul>
                    <li><i>Accumulated Demerit Points</i> – Many traffic tickets come with demerit points. If you are convicted of these   offences, the points are added to your driving record. If the total number of points reaches 15 or more, or 9     or more for new drivers, your license will be suspended for 30 or 60 days respectively. Even before these   thresholds, you may be asked to attend a meeting to discuss if your license should be suspended. This is why  it is so important to hire a traffic ticket lawyer to fight every ticket.</li>
                    <li><i>Failure to Appear/Pay</i> – If you fail to appear at meetings with the Ministry or if you do not pay    outstanding fines, this can also lead to a driver’s license suspension. This does not mean pay fines as soon   as you receive them; paying is an admission of guilt. Consult with one of our traffic ticket attorneys first. </li>
                    <li><i>Criminal Driving Offences</i> – A criminal driving offence conviction, such as a driving under the influence    conviction, can lead to automatic suspension of your license.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4 class="first">Do Not Drive with a Suspended License</h4>
                    <p>Driving without a license is a serious offence in Toronto and throughout Ontario. A driving under    suspension ticket can lead to an extended suspension, large fines, and even imprisonment. Being unaware of     your suspension is not an acceptable defense for these charges, making it all the more crucial that you stay    well informed of your driving record.</p>
                    <h4 class="first">How Get Legal Help Assists with License Suspension</h4>
                    <p>We  help you fight the charges that could lead to having your driver’s license suspended.</p>
                    <p>If you receive a driving under suspension ticket, you can file an appeal. In some cases, suspensions are     lifted before appeals are even approved, and an approved appeal allows the suspension to be cleared from your   record. Let our experienced criminal lawyers, ex-police officers, and other skilled traffic ticket legal  professionals draft and submit a strong appeal on your behalf.</p>
                    <p>If your license was suspended due to unpaid fines, we can help you get extensions on these fines, allowing   you to structure a more feasible repayment schedule. At Get Legal Help, we also keep our services cost    effective, allowing you to receive services at a great value.</p>
                    <p>Call Get Legal Help at 1-866-431-5763 as early as possible if your license has been suspended in Toronto     or any of the surrounding regions. We will help you through this confusing process. </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3>Fail to Provide Documents (Permits, Validations, Plates, Drivers Licence)</h3>
                    <hr/>
                    <p>Forgot your wallet at home this morning? STOP. You may have just increased your insurance premiums. NPTT Legal Services has a 100% success rate at having these types of charges dropped.</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Drive Motor Vehicle No Permit</h4>
                    <p>Here’s what you need to know:</p>
                    <p>Drive Motor Vehicle No Permit:<br>
                    a) No permit (Ownership)<br>
                    b) No Currently Validated Permit</p>
                    <p>You must have a validation sticker on the back of the plate portion of your ownership to prove that your plates are valid.                   </p>
                    <p>Note: The Validation sticker serial numbers on the back of your permit should match the validation serial numbers on your                    car’s plate.</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Drive Motor Vehicle No Permit Ontario &amp; The Law</h4>
                    <p>HTA 7(4)(a)<br>
                    No person shall drive a motor vehicle on a highway unless,<br>
                    (a) there exist a currently validated permit for the vehicle</p>
                    <h4 class="second">The Penalty in Ontario</h4>
                    <p>$85 plus Government Surcharge</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Drive Motor Vehicle No Validation</h4>
                    <p>You cannot drive a vehicle in Ontario that has an expired validation sticker. Even if the validation is in the mail on its way, you can be ticketed.</p>
                    <p>Drive Motor Vehicle:<br>
                    a) No Validation on Plate<br>
                    b) Validation Improperly Affixed</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Drive Motor Vehicle No Validation Ontario &amp; The Law</h4>
                    <p>HTA 7(1)(c)(i)<br>
                    No person shall drive a motor vehicle on a highway unless,<br>
                    c) evidence of the current validation of the permit is affixed, in the prescribed manner to…<br>
                    (i) one of the number plates mentioned…displayed on the vehicle or<br>
                    (ii) to a mini-plate attached to the number plate exposed on the rear of the vehicle…</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Drive Motor Vehicle No Validation Ontario Penalty &amp; Ontario</h4>
                    <p>$85 plus Government Surcharge</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Traffic Violation: No Validation</h4>
                    <p>You can not drive a vehicle in Ontario that has an expired validation sticker. Even if the validation is in the mail on its way to you, you can be ticketed.</p>
                    <p>Drive Motor Vehicle:<br>
                    a) Validation Improperly Affixed<br>
                    b) No Validation on Plate</p>
                    <h4 class="second">The Penalty in Ontario</h4>
                    <p>$85 plus Government Surcharge</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Drive Motor Vehicle: Improper Plates</h4>
                    <p>Did you know that you can be ticketed for having a plate light that is not white in the Province of Ontario? Neon License plates lights are prohibited and your plates can not be covered.</p>
                    <p>Drive Motor Vehicle:<br>
                    a) No Plates<br>
                    b) Fail to Display 2 Plates<br>
                    c) Plates improperly displayed</p>
                    <h4 class="second">Drive Motor Vehicle: Improper Plates Ontario and The Law</h4>
